From: OpenWrt W1700K build
Subject: [PATCH] pmdomain: mediatek: allow AIROHA_CPU_PM_DOMAIN under ARCH_AIROHA

The drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/Kconfig menu is gated on ARCH_MEDIATEK,
which hides AIROHA_CPU_PM_DOMAIN (the Airoha CPU PM domain driver living
in this directory for historical reasons) on Airoha SoCs that set
ARCH_AIROHA but not ARCH_MEDIATEK.

Without this driver, the airoha-cpufreq driver cannot attach an OPP-set
PM domain to cpu0 and defers probe forever, leaving CPUs at the
boot-default 1.2 GHz on Airoha EN7581 / AN7581 platforms (W1700K etc).

Widen the menu dependency to also accept ARCH_AIROHA.

--- a/drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/Kconfig
@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only

 menu "MediaTek PM Domains"
-	depends on ARCH_MEDIATEK || COMPILE_TEST
+	depends on ARCH_MEDIATEK || ARCH_AIROHA || COMPILE_TEST

 config MTK_SCPSYS
 	bool "MediaTek SCPSYS Support"
